<?xml version="1.0"?>
<h:html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2002/xforms" xmlns:ev="http://www.w3.org/2001/xml-events" xmlns:h="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" xmlns:jr="http://openrosa.org/javarosa" xmlns:orx="http://openrosa.org/xforms" xmlns:xsd="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema">
  <h:head>
    <h:title>infant-child</h:title>
    <model>
      <itext>
        <translation lang="en">
          <text id="/infant-child/child_danger_signs/danger_signs_intro_note:label">
            <value>I'm not going to screen your chlid for danger signs. Observe the child and discuss each danger sign with the mother and child.</value>
          </text>
          <text id="/infant-child/child_danger_signs/neonatal_screening/neonatal_danger_signs/cold:label">
            <value>Cold or low temperature</value>
          </text>
          <text id="/infant-child/child_danger_signs/neonatal_screening/neonatal_danger_signs/cord_bleeding:label">
            <value>Cord red, bleeding, or draining pus</value>
          </text>
          <text id="/infant-child/child_danger_signs/neonatal_screening/neonatal_danger_signs/diarrhea:label">
            <value>Diarrhea</value>
          </text>
          <text id="/infant-child/child_danger_signs/neonatal_screening/neonatal_danger_signs/difficulty_fast_breathing:label">
            <value>Difficulty or fast breathing (Two counts of 60 breaths or more in one minute)</value>
          </text>
          <text id="/infant-child/child_danger_signs/neonatal_screening/neonatal_danger_signs/excessive_crying:label">
            <value>Excessive crying or restlessness for more than one hour, non-stop</value>
          </text>
          <text id="/infant-child/child_danger_signs/neonatal_screening/neonatal_danger_signs/excessive_vomiting:label">
            <value>Excessive vomiting</value>
          </text>
          <text id="/infant-child/child_danger_signs/neonatal_screening/neonatal_danger_signs/eyes_pus:label">
            <value>Eyes draining pus</value>
          </text>
          <text id="/infant-child/child_danger_signs/neonatal_screening/neonatal_danger_signs/fever:label">
            <value>Fever or high temperature</value>
          </text>
          <text id="/infant-child/child_danger_signs/neonatal_screening/neonatal_danger_signs/had_convulsions:label">
            <value>Had convulsions</value>
          </text>
          <text id="/infant-child/child_danger_signs/neonatal_screening/neonatal_danger_signs/no_movement:label">
            <value>Movement only when stimulated, or no movement even on stimulation</value>
          </text>
          <text id="/infant-child/child_danger_signs/neonatal_screening/neonatal_danger_signs/none:label">
            <value>None of the above</value>
          </text>
          <text id="/infant-child/child_danger_signs/neonatal_screening/neonatal_danger_signs/not_able_feed:label">
            <value>Not able to feed since birth, or stopped feeding well</value>
          </text>
          <text id="/infant-child/child_danger_signs/neonatal_screening/neonatal_danger_signs/skin_boils:label">
            <value>Skin boils</value>
          </text>
          <text id="/infant-child/child_danger_signs/neonatal_screening/neonatal_danger_signs/yellow_pale_palms:label">
            <value>Yellow or pale palms and soles (hands and feet), and lips. Soles should be red/pink.</value>
          </text>
          <text id="/infant-child/child_danger_signs/neonatal_screening/neonatal_danger_signs:label">
            <value>SAY: I'm now going to screen your baby for neonatal danger signs.

Observe and discuss each danger sign with the mother and child. Select any of the danger signs that the baby has right now</value>
          </text>
          <text id="/infant-child/child_danger_signs/neonatal_screening:label">
            <value>Neonatal Danger Signs Screening</value>
          </text>
          <text id="/infant-child/child_danger_signs:label">
            <value>Child Danger Signs Screening</value>
          </text>
          <text id="/infant-child/child_visit_intro_note:label">
            <value>SEMA: Habari mama? Kama tulivyozungumza wakati wa matembeleo yetu yaliyopita kuwa ntakuja kukutembelea kwa ajili ya kujua maendeleo na afya ya mtoto/watoto, na pia kujadiliana na wewe pamoja na familia juu ya malezi na makuzi bora ya mtoto/watoto wako. Nafahamu kuwa unajua jinsi ya kumtunza mtoto wako na kumkuza vizuri, lakini hii ni kama nyongeza tu ya elimu kutokana na ongezeko la maradhi na matatizo mbali mbali yanayoweza kudhoofisha afya na makuzi bora ya mtoto.</value>
          </text>
          <text id="/infant-child/consent/child_consent_today/no:label">
            <value>No</value>
          </text>
          <text id="/infant-child/consent/child_consent_today/yes:label">
            <value>Yes</value>
          </text>
          <text id="/infant-child/consent/child_consent_today:label">
            <value>Greet the family and invite others to join the conversation as appropriate.

SAY: I'd like to enroll <output value=" /infant-child/child_name "/> into infant and child services. I'll do a first check-up on their health today, and them return at important times as they grow up to make sure they are healthy and well. Is that OK?</value>
          </text>
          <text id="/infant-child/consent:label">
            <value>Consent</value>
          </text>
          <text id="/infant-child/first_visit_6_months/birthweight_on_child_card/no:label">
            <value>No</value>
          </text>
          <text id="/infant-child/first_visit_6_months/birthweight_on_child_card/yes:label">
            <value>Yes</value>
          </text>
          <text id="/infant-child/first_visit_6_months/birthweight_on_child_card:label">
            <value>Is the birthweight written on the child card?</value>
          </text>
          <text id="/infant-child/first_visit_6_months/child_birthweight:jr:constraintMsg">
            <value>Enter a number between 0.5 and 7 KG</value>
          </text>
          <text id="/infant-child/first_visit_6_months/child_birthweight:label">
            <value>Enter brithweight of the child, in KG</value>
          </text>
          <text id="/infant-child/first_visit_6_months/child_card_available/no:label">
            <value>No</value>
          </text>
          <text id="/infant-child/first_visit_6_months/child_card_available/yes:label">
            <value>Yes</value>
          </text>
          <text id="/infant-child/first_visit_6_months/child_card_available:label">
            <value>Is the child card available?</value>
          </text>
          <text id="/infant-child/first_visit_6_months/child_size_birth/large:label">
            <value>Large</value>
          </text>
          <text id="/infant-child/first_visit_6_months/child_size_birth/regular:label">
            <value>Regular</value>
          </text>
          <text id="/infant-child/first_visit_6_months/child_size_birth/small:label">
            <value>Small</value>
          </text>
          <text id="/infant-child/first_visit_6_months/child_size_birth:label">
            <value>Approximately how large was the baby at birth?</value>
          </text>
          <text id="/infant-child/first_visit_6_months/delivery_location/at_home:label">
            <value>At home</value>
          </text>
          <text id="/infant-child/first_visit_6_months/delivery_location/health_facility:label">
            <value>In a health facility</value>
          </text>
          <text id="/infant-child/first_visit_6_months/delivery_location/on_way_health_facility:label">
            <value>On the way to the health facility</value>
          </text>
          <text id="/infant-child/first_visit_6_months/delivery_location:label">
            <value>Where was the child born?</value>
          </text>
          <text id="/infant-child/first_visit_6_months/encourage_small_baby_note:label">
            <value>_Look child card and/or KMC booklet for next scheduled follow-up visit. Advise mother to return to the facility for scheduled follow up visits_</value>
          </text>
          <text id="/infant-child/first_visit_6_months/has_received_small_baby_services/no:label">
            <value>No</value>
          </text>
          <text id="/infant-child/first_visit_6_months/has_received_small_baby_services/yes:label">
            <value>Yes</value>
          </text>
          <text id="/infant-child/first_visit_6_months/has_received_small_baby_services:label">
            <value>ASK: Have you received small baby services at the hospital?</value>
          </text>
          <text id="/infant-child/first_visit_6_months/normal_baby_note:label">
            <value>This is a normal size baby and needs normal care. You will learn about care for the normal baby in later sessions.</value>
          </text>
          <text id="/infant-child/first_visit_6_months/refer_small_baby_note:label">
            <value>_Refer to nearest KMC ward_</value>
          </text>
          <text id="/infant-child/first_visit_6_months/small_baby_note:label">
            <value>This child is a small baby and extra care and attention is needed from both CHV and family. We will talk about some of the special care your baby needs.</value>
          </text>
          <text id="/infant-child/first_visit_6_months:label">
            <value>First Infant Visit</value>
          </text>
          <text id="/infant-child/inputs/user/contact_id:label">
            <value>Contact ID of the logged in user</value>
          </text>
          <text id="/infant-child/inputs/user/facility_id:label">
            <value>Facility ID for the parent user</value>
          </text>
          <text id="/infant-child/inputs/user/name:label">
            <value>Name of the logged in user</value>
          </text>
        </translation>
